<HEADLINE> Chirac Says Russia and U.N. Should Play Role </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 12 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
said on Monday that Russia and the United Nations should play
their roles in solving the Yugoslav crisis, while calling on NATO
to continue its military pressure on Belgrade.
</P>
<P>
In his third radio-television speech since the beginning of
NATO campaign against Yugoslavia, Chirac said that the Western
allies "widely agree" that the U.N. Security Council and Russia
should be fully involved in the process of seeking a political
solution to the Yugoslav crisis.
</P>
<P>
"All the discussions I had in the past several days have made
appear...a wide convergence of views on the role of the Security
Council and the necessary association of Russia in the search for
a political solution to the conflict," he said.
</P>
<P>
He again justified the NATO airstrikes against Yugoslavia and
said that the bombings are producing effects.
</P>
<P>
"There is not any doubt as for the responsibility of the Serb
regime which is the origin of this crisis and which continues
methodically its criminal action of ethnic cleansing," he said.
</P>
<P>
He called on the international community to act with emergency
in favor of the displaced people in Kosovo while maintaining a
military pressure on Belgrade until it has satisfied "the just
moral and political demands."
</P>
<P>
The French president said that more aid should be sent to
Albania, Macedonia and Montenegro which are subjected to a massive
influx of refugees from Kosovo.  
</P>
</TEXT>
