<HEADLINE> Three die in truck crash in Ghana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
NAIROBI, April 12 (Xinhua) - - Three persons including a
40-year old driver of a DAF articulated truck died instantly when
the long vehicle hit a bridge on river Pra at Assin-Praso at the
weekend, the Ghana News Agency (GNA) reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
A 17 year-old girl who was walking on the bridge at the time
of the accident was killed in addition to the driver's mate.
</P>
<P>
According to Assin-Praso police, the truck, loaded with bags
of cement from the Western Port of Takoradi to Kumasi was at top
speed when crossing the toll bridge at Assin-Praso, and hit the
bridge.
</P>
<P>
 The impact was so great that the head of the truck got off
from the main trailer causing severe damage to the bridge.
</P>
</TEXT>
