<HEADLINE> Seven Ecuadorian Soldiers killed by Helicopter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Seven soldiers that traveled on
Superpuma 460 helicopter of the Ecuadorian army died when their
craft fell to ground on Sunday, Ecuador's Defense Ministry said
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The helicopter crashed while it carried members of the
Demarcation Commission checking the placement of milestone 13 at
Condor Mountain Range, along the Ecuador and Peru border.
</P>
<P>
Up till now have been found the bodies of the pilots and
another soldier with the help of a helicopter from the Task Force
of Military Observers for Ecuador and Peru (MOMEP). 
</P>
</TEXT>
