<HEADLINE> Middle East Economic Briefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 12 (Xinhua) -- The following are economic briefs
from Middle East countries.
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Egypt will participate in the Arab convention and fair
for food and packing industries due to be held in Beirut on June
10-19.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the chamber of printing and packing at the
Federation of Egyptian Industries Ahmed Atef said some 200
companies from Egypt, Lebanon, Syria, Jordan, Saudi Arabia,
Kuwait, the United Arab Emirates and Tunisia will participate in
the fair.
</P>
<P>
Atef also said the fair will offer participants
opportunities to learn about the diversity and qualities of Arab
foodstuffs and will widely open the door for inter-Arab trade
promotion, the Arabic newspaper Al Hayat reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Atef disclosed that on the sidelines of the fair, a convention
will be held to discuss ways of funding and promoting inter-Arab
trade.
</P>
<P>
TRIPOLI -- Libyan ministers of petroleum and economy will
attend an international conference later this month on the
prospect of investment in Libya and the impact of the
U.N. sanctions.
</P>
<P>
The conference hosted by Switzerland is the first of its kind
since the suspension of the seven-year-old sanctions on April 5,
the Al Hayat said Monday.
</P>
<P>
At the conference, Libyan ministers will introduce the
petroleum and economic developments in Libya and the aftermath of
the sanctions, which cost Libya more than 26 billion U.S. dollars
in losses.
</P>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY -- Saudi Arabia Monday decided to open duty free
shops in the county's three international airports.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made at a weekly cabinet session chaired by
Saudi King Fahd Ibn Abdul-Aziz in the Saudi western city of Jeddah.
</P>
<P>
Only goods sold in the domestic markets will be allowed into
these shops. Alcohol, strictly banned in the kingdom by Islamic
teachings, will not be sold in these shops.
</P>
<P>
The Saudi cabinet also agreed to sell locally-made goods along
with foreign ones in the shops.
</P>
<P>
Of the 28 airports in Saudi Arabia, there are three
international airports, namely Riyadh international airport,
Jeddah international airport and the eastern Dharan international
airport.
</P>
<P>
SANNA -- Yemen has embarked on the technical studies of the
additional works of the second stage of Maarib dam undertaken by
the Indian engineering and construction company and financed by a
grant extended by the Abu Dhabi development fund.
</P>
<P>
According to the feasibility studies of the project, the first
stage covers 1,750 hectares of agricultural land, which will rise
to 7,500 hectares upon the completion of the second stage.
</P>
<P>
It will directly benefit 2000 families and will improve the
efficiency of irrigation by 62 percent, The Al Hayat reported
Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
