<HEADLINE> Iranian Majlis Speaker Denounces NATO Strikes on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Majlis (parliament)
Speaker Ali Akbar Nateq Nouri here on Monday denounced the North
Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) for launching airstrikes on
Yugoslavia "without any consultation with the Muslim countries."
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with visiting Saudi Foreign Minister Saud
Al-Faisal, Nouri said that NATO strikes on Yugoslavia brought
about massive displacement of the Muslim Albanians in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
According to the Islamic Republic News Agency, the two
officials also exchanged views on bilateral relations,
parliamentary cooperation, the Afghan issue and endeavors to
resolve problems in the Muslim countries.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the continuation of fighting in Afghanistan, Nouri
said "secret hands" have always tried to hinder unity and
solidarity in the Islamic world. He did not elaborate, however.
</P>
<P>
Iran and Saudi Arabia, as two important and strategic
countries of the region, will help bolster unity and solidarity in
the Islamic world through deepening their relations, he said.
</P>
<P>
On his part, Al-Faisal said he was happy to see further
expansion of relations and cooperation between the two nations.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed hope that the Muslim countries would make
more efforts to solve the problems in Kosovo and Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Al-Faisal arrived here Monday morning to arrange the
ground-breaking visit of Iranian President Mohammad Khatami to
Riyadh. He also held talks with his Iranian counterpart Kamal
Kharrazi on bilateral relations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
