<HEADLINE> Kuwaiti, U.S. Schools to Boost Environmental </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait and the United States
signed here Monday a Glob agreement aimed at increasing
environmental cooperation among schools in the two countries, as
well as in other countries.
</P>
<P>
The deal was inked by Kuwaiti Minister for Education and
Higher Education Abdul-Aziz Al-Ghanem and U.S. ambassador in
Kuwait James Larroco.
</P>
<P>
The agreement will allow Kuwaiti students to contact with
others via the Internet to exchange information on environment and
enable them to be acquainted with life in other countries, Larroco
told Kuwait News Agency after the signing ceremony.
</P>
<P>
For his part, Al-Ghanem said "we cannot live in a world
without cooperation with others and exchanging views and
information."
</P>
<P>
Glob, a U.S.-chaired international program for environmental
education, allows students to contact their friends worldwide to
discuss environmental issues.
</P>
<P>
More than 5,000 schools of 70 countries are members in
Glob. 
</P>
</TEXT>
