<HEADLINE> Congo Rebels Claim Seize Govt Town </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Congolese Coalition for Democracy (CCD), which is fighting
in eastern Congo (K) with supports from Rwanda, claimed that it
had taken Lubefu, a small town about 180 kilometers from
Mbuji-Mayi.
</P>
<P>
The Congolese rebels have been fighting toward the strategic
towns of Mbuji-Mayi and Kabinda since March in the war against
President Laurent Kabila's forces, which are backed by troops from
Zimbabwe, Angola and Namibia.
</P>
