<HEADLINE> Over 9,000 Kosovar Refugees Arrive in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 12 (Xinhua) -- A total of 9,147 Kosovar refugees
have arrived in Turkey for shelter since NATO launched air strikes
against Yugoslavia on March 24.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued Monday by the Turkish Interior Ministry
said that among the Kosovar refugees, 3,275 were placed in the
guest house in the northwestern province of Kirklareli.
</P>
<P>
Forty-four medical workers including six doctors have been sent
to the guest house and two mobile hospitals were set up in the
region.
</P>
<P>
Two Kosovar refugees died, two women gave birth and 11 were
treated in Kirklareli, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
Turkey, a NATO member, supports the alliance's bombings against
Yugoslavia to press Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic to allow
NATO forces into Kosovo to police a peace deal that will give
broad autonomy to ethnic Albanians who make up 90 percent of the
population there.
</P>
<P>
A total of 11 Turkish warplanes stationed in NATO's bases in
Italy have joined the NATO air campaign on Yugoslavia. 
