<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Zhu Visits Chicago Mercantile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHICAGO, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji Monday
visited the Chicago Mercantile Exchange(CME), an international
marketplace trading futures and options on a variety of products.
</P>
<P>
Premier Zhu, accompanied by CME Chairman Scott Gordon, toured
the CME's two trading floors where buyers and sellers meet to
trade futures contracts and options on futures through the process
of "open outcry".
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Premier also rang a ceremonial bell in the
exchange's colorful and world-famous Eurodollar trading pit where
Eurodollar futures traded.
</P>
<P>
Eurodollars are short-term interest rate contracts --
three-month instruments trading up to 10 years into the future.
They represent American dollars on deposit in overseas
institutions.
</P>
<P>
The CME's Eurodollar futures contract is often the most
actively traded futures contract in the world.
</P>
<P>
The CME Chairman presented a red trading jacket to Zhu Rongji,
the first Chinese Premier to visit the place.  
</P>
