<HEADLINE> Ozone Layer Protection Conference Held in Lesotho </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Delegates from more than 20
English-speaking African countries are meeting in Lesotho to
discuss destruction of an invisible blanket which protects the
earth from direct rays of the Sun, the ozone layer, Radio Lesotho
reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The participants will review progress to implement the Montreal
Protocol in the English-speaking African countries.
</P>
<P>
The five-day conference, which opened Monday morning in Maseru,
Lesotho' s capital, was organized by the United Nations
Environment Program and the Lesotho government.
</P>
<P>
Science experts have warned that life on earth is in danger due
to destruction of the ozone layer, causing droughts, floods and
other adverse weather conditions.
</P>
<P>
The ozone layer is part of the atmosphere which absorbs most of
 the harmful radiation from the Sun. 
</P>
