<HEADLINE> Iran Calls for Cooperation With Saudi Arabia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Former Iranian President Hashemi
Rafsanjani on Monday called for further cooperation between Iran
and Saudi Arabia to stabilize oil prices in the world market.
</P>
<P>
If Iran and Saudi Arabia adopt a unified stance in the
Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC), it will
produce very effective results, Rafsanjani told visiting Saudi
Foreign Minister Saud Al-Faisal.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Tehran-Riyadh cooperation would encourage other
oil producing states toward more cooperation, the Islamic
Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Stability in the oil market demanded political determination
of the oil producing countries, said Rafsanjani, current chairman
of the powerful advisory State Expediency Council.
</P>
<P>
He called on OPEC to draw up specific plans and make necessary
forecasts so as to protect the production and sale of oil.
</P>
<P>
Al-Faisal said that Iran and Saudi Arabia, in light of their
strategic situation in the region, can forge a more suitable
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The cooperation between the two countries in the area of oil
was a successful example of mutual cooperation in OPEC, he said,
expressing regret that the OPEC policies in the past were
monopolistic and that overproduction was the cause of rivalry
between the member states.
</P>
<P>
He also hoped for stronger cooperation among the OPEC members,
particularly between Iran and Saudi Arabia to stabilize the oil
market. 
</P>
