<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNDP to Help West African Countries Implement Arms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 12 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Development Program (UNDP) said here on Monday it had decided to
work with the Organization of African Unity and the Economic
Commission of West African States to implement an arms moratorium
in 16 West African countries.
</P>
<P>
UNDP said the goal is to reduce the number of small arms and
weapons that fuel the region's conflicts.
</P>
<P>
UNDP is providing 2.1 million U.S. dollars in funding for the
13 million dollars effort.
</P>
<P>
The arms moratorium has been launched as part of UNDP's
Program for Coordination and Assistance for Security and
Development in Africa, which addresses security challenges in the
region that are linked to the proliferation of small arms.
</P>
<P>
Activities under the moratorium include the establishment of
arms database, education and public awareness campaigns, training
for security forces, a review of legislation governing the
purchase of small arms, and the collection and destruction of
weapons.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
