<HEADLINE> Chinese Top Legislator Arrives in Thailand on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHIANG MAI, Thailand, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, Chairman of
the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress of China
(NPC), arrived in this northern city of Thailand on Tuesday for a
five-day official visit to the country.
</P>
<P>
Li is here at the invitation of President of the Thai National
Assembly Wan Muhamad Nor Matha. It is his first visit to Thailand
as chairman of the NPC Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
First Deputy Speaker of the House of Representatives of
Thailand Sonphon Phetsawang, Secretary-General of the National
Assembly Sirilak Panbumrungkit, Chiang Mai Governor Pravit
Sisophon, Chinese Ambassador to Thailand Fu Xuezhang, as well as
representatives of Chinese nationals in Chiang Mai welcomed Li and
his wife Zhu Lin at the airport.
</P>
<P>
Thailand is the six and the last leg of Li's current six-nation
trip, which has already taken him to Greece, Turkey, Syria,
Pakistan and Bangladesh.
</P>
<P>
During his visit in Thailand, Li will call on King of Thailand
Bhumibol Adulyadej, and meet Prime Minister Chuan Leekpai and
Speaker of the House of Representatives Wan Muhamad Nor Matha and
Speaker of the Senate Meechai Ruchupan.
</P>
<P>
Li and his entourage is expected to leave Chiang Mai for the
capital city of Bangkok on Friday before going back home on
Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
