<HEADLINE> Urgent: India Flight Tests Unmanned Air Vehicle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 13 (Xinhua) -- India on Tuesday successfully
flight tested its unmanned air vehicle "Nishant" from the interim
test range in Orissa State of eastern India.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said that the pilotless aircraft is
developed for conducting military surveillance, training and
performing discrete aerial reconnaissance including target
acquisition.
</P>
<P>
The pilotless air vehicle carried with various kinds of
payloads including a camera, integrated telemetry, telecommand and
tracking system designs, official sources said.
</P>
<P>
Two days earlier, India test-fired its nuclear capable "Agni
11" ballistic missile with a strike range of over 2,000 km.
</P>
</TEXT>
