<BODY>
<HEADLINE> British MPs Condemn NATO Atrocity in Bombing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 13 (Xinhua) -- A group of British Parliament
Members (MPs) on Tuesday condemned the killing of civilians by the
NATO bombing of a passenger train in southern Serbia as an
"atrocity".
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued by the Committee for Peace in the
Balkans, which is chaired by Alice Mahon, a Labor Party MP, the
MPs said "NATO is now killing Yugoslav civilians virtually every
day in its undeclared and illegal war."
</P>
<P>
"The statement by NATO secretary general, Javier Solana, that
NATO is not waging a war on Yugoslavia and has no quarrel with the
people of that country, must sound like a sick joke to those whose
friends, relatives and children are being killed by NATO bombs,"
the statement said.
</P>
<P>
"If they are not at war, what they are doing is straightforward
murder. There are penalties for people who just go out and murder
other people," Alice Mahon said.
</P>
<P>
"What is humanitarian about the bombing of civilians on a
passenger train? There is no military solution to the complex
problems of Yugoslavia and I call again for NATO to stop the
bombing," the statement added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
