<HEADLINE> New Flight From Xining To Lhasa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, April 13 (Xinhua) -- A flight linking Xining, the
capital of northwest China's Qinghai Province, with Lhasa, the
capital of the Tibet Autonomous Region, is scheduled to begin on
April 16.
</P>
<P>
China Southwest Airlines, which is based in Chengdu, the
capital of Sichuan Province, will fly the 1,558-kilometer air
route using a Boeing 757-200.
</P>
<P>
The flight time between the two cities is just over 2 hours,
compared with a 3-day journey by bus.
</P>
<P>
Flights between Lhasa and Golmud, another major city in western
Qinghai, began in 1975, but were halted in 1985. 
</P>
