GENEVA -- The World Intellectual Property Organization (WIPO)
will hold the first meeting of the Policy Advisory Commission (PAC)
on April 15, the United Nations agency announced Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting to be chaired by Idris, PAC members will offer
their insights on the significance of placing intellectual
property in a wider economic, social, and cultural context.
</P>
<P>
