<P>
TIRANA -- The Macedonian government has decided that it will
continue to airlift Kosovo refugees to third countries, Macedonian
Informative Agency reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The report said that by Monday, Macedonia had forwarded 5,992
Kosovo refugees to Turkey, the Netherlands, Germany and Israel
through air corridor.
</P>
<P>
Reports said that a total of 120,000 Kosovo refugees have found
their way into Macedonia. Most of them have been settled down in
the homes of local residents. The rest, nearly 50,000 refugees,
are living in refugee camps. (Macedonia-Kosovo-Refugees)
</P>
<P>
