MOSCOW -- Russian Foreign Ministry on Tuesday released a
statement slamming NATO's bombing of a Yugoslav passenger train,
saying the destruction of civilian targets could not be tolerated.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that the train was hit by a NATO missile on
Monday when it was crossing a bridge on its way from Leskovac.
</P>
<P>
According to Yugoslav rescue officials, 10 people were killed
and 16 injured in the attack, during which one carriage of the
train was destroyed completely. (Russia-Kosovo-Train) 
