<HEADLINE> Australia to Test Visiting Foreign Athletes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Foreign athletes who train in
Australia prior to the 2000 Sydney Olympic Games will be subject
to the same doping tests as Australians, the country's national
drug agency said Tuesday in Melbourne.
</P>
<P>
Natalie Howson, chief executive of the government-funded
Australia Sports Drug Agency (ASDA) said high-risk sports and high-
risk athletes would be targeted by ASDA.
</P>
<P>
She said 70 percent of ASDA's testing will be conducted out of
competition.
</P>
<P>
If ASDA finds any positive results, ASDA can inform the
relevant Australian sporting organization which could influence
its foreign counterpart to ban its athlete, Howson added. 
</P>
