<HEADLINE> Turkish Police Seize 24 Kilograms of Heroin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Turkish police have seized 24.5
kilograms of heroin in one anti-drug operation in southern
Turkey, the semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the police found the heroin in the city
of Adana in southern Turkey.
</P>
<P>
It was believed that the drug smugglers wanted to send the
heroin to Germany, said the agency.
</P>
<P>
Seven suspected smugglers were arrested for alleged involvement
in this case.
</P>
<P>
Turkish police conducted 2,928 operations against
drug-trafficking last year and seized 10 tons of drugs, including
5.3 tons of hashish and 3.8 tons of heroin.
</P>
<P>
Turkey is on a transit route of drugs from the border area of
Afghanistan and Pakistan to Europe. 
</P>
