<HEADLINE> Macedonia to Continue Airlifting Kosovo Refugees to Third Nations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The Macedonian government has
decided that it will continue to airlift Kosovo refugees to third
countries, Macedonian Informative Agency reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The report said that by Monday, Macedonia had forwarded 5,992
Kosovo refugees to Turkey, the Netherlands, Germany and Israel
through air corridor.
</P>
<P>
Macedonian Deputy Prime Ministers Radmilak Iprijanova and
Bedredin Ibrahimi and Defense Minister Nikola Kljusev said Monday,
after a meeting on the refugee situation, that their country would
continue with the move of airlifting refugees to third nations.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said that a total of 120,000 Kosovo
refugees have found their way into Macedonia. Most of them have
been settled down in the homes of local residents. The rest,
nearly 50,000 refugees, are living in refugee camps.
</P>
<P>
The Macedonian defense minister said that his country still has
the capacity to receive another 6,000 refugees. 
</P>
