<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Feature: Myanmar Celebrates Thingyan Water Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, April 13 (Xinhua) -- As beautiful girls in colorful
festive dresses are singing and dancing at the central water
throwing pandal in front of the Yangon Mayor's Office building,
the three-day 1999 Maha (Great) Yangon Thingyan Water Festival
began here Tuesday afternoon, one day ahead of the Water festival.
</P>
<P>
The festival, part of which is also Myanmar's New Year Day,
started with merry-makers throwing water on people and motor
vehicles passing by. As a matter of fact, water throwing is a
traditional way of expressing blessings of the Myanmar people.
</P>
<P>
Nowadays, apart from celebrating the festival in the
traditional way, people learned to use water gun and water pipe to
sprinkle water on one another. Even foreign diplomats and tourists
joined the local people to mark the occasion.
</P>
<P>
Although the country is in difficulties economically this year,
the festive atmosphere remains as high as in the previous years.
</P>
<P>
Water throwing pandals were built in various townships in the
capital and both traditional and modern entertainment programs
were presented by popular singers and dancers. Song and dance
competitions are also held at some pandals.
</P>
<P>
The water festival will be celebrated for three days in the
country. The New Year Day will be marked on Saturday when water
throwing comes to an end.
</P>
<P>
Festive activities also include offering of food to monks,
washing and cleaning of monasteries, pagoda platforms and images
of the Buddha, filling water pots in monasteries, washing of heads
of elderly people with scented water and offering them neat, clean
and warm clothes as a gesture of respect.
</P>
<P>
Water is a symbol of cleanliness. So people here believe that
celebration of the Water Festival can wash away evils of the old
days and bring the people into the New Year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
