<HEADLINE> Lotus Festival In Southern Chinese City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The 1999 China Lotus Festival is
scheduled to begin July 8 in Yueyang, in Hunan Province.
</P>
<P>
The three-month festival, the first to be held in the city, is
one of the activities of the National Tourism Administration's
ecological tourism year.
</P>
<P>
The festival will be held at Tuanhu Lake, which is known for
its more than 333 hectares of lotus. Nearly 100 varieties and the
many bird species like the red-crown crane and wild swan have made
the lake a scenic spot.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of tourists from a dozen countries visit the scenic
spot every year. 
</P>
