<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-Dutch Seminar on Water Control Begins in Beijing (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Senior officials and experts from
China and the Netherlands gathered here today for a seminar on
water management and cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Sponsored by the governments of China and the Netherlands, the
high-level seminar attracted Her Majesty Queen Beatrix of the
Netherlands who is on a state visit to China, Dutch Deputy Prime
Minister and Minister of Economic Affairs Annemarie Jorritsma,
China's Vice Premier Wen Jiabao, and other senior officials from
both countries.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from China's Ministry of Water Resources,
Ministry of Construction, State Forestry Bureau, State
Environmental Protection Administration, State Administration of
Foreign Experts Affairs, State Headquarters of Flood Control and
Drought Relief, the water resources committees of China's six
major rivers, provincial authorities and experts all are attending
the seminar, which will conclude tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
Dutch representatives include members of the Ministry of
Transport, Public Works and Water Management, the Ministry of
Economic Affairs, the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, and banks and
companies with interests in the water sector.
</P>
<P>
Seminar topics include integrated water and river management,
flood control policy and planning, dredging, dike construction and
engineering, water supply and quality, and sanitation.
</P>
</TEXT>
