<HEADLINE> International Conference on Long-Distance Education Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- An international conference on
long-distance education and educational development in the 21st
century opened today in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
About 100 experts and scholars from a number of international
organizations including UNESCO, and 15 countries and regions
attended the conference, which was organized by Qinghua University.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony, Vice-Minister of Personnel Xu
Songtao said modern long-distance education, characterized by
computer network technology and multi-media digital technology,
has promoted the application of knowledge and will have a profound
impact on the development of education in the next century.
</P>
<P>
Like other countries, China has been increasing investment and
intensifying research in this regard, said the deputy minister.
</P>
<P>
According to Xu, about 40 percent of the country's scientists
and researchers now participate in adult education such as on-the-
job training courses, and that since 1990, some 70 million people
have attended these types of classes.
</P>
<P>
During the three-day conference, participants will discuss such
topics as long-distance study's impact on education and social
development, new concepts in long-distance education and study,
technical support for long-distance education, subject-matter for
long-distance education, and the management of long-distance
education.  
</P>
</TEXT>
