<HEADLINE> Roundup: Dutch Queen's Visit to Boost Trade Ties with China (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin in his meeting with the visiting
queen yesterday evening, said her current visit will definitely
cement the understanding and friendship between the peoples of the
two countries, as well as consolidate Sino-Dutch ties.
</P>
<P>
Accompanying the queen, Dutch Deputy Prime Minister and
Minister of Economic Affairs Annemarie Jorritsma-Lebbink is
leading a large trade delegation of presidents and general
managers of more than 50 renowned Dutch companies to hold friendly
and constructive talks with their Chinese counterparts on the
promotion of bilateral economic and trade ties.
</P>
<P>
The visit by the queen and the Dutch trade delegation fully
demonstrates the country's wishes to expand economic and trade
cooperation with China, said an official of the Chinese Ministry
of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
China and the Netherlands have witnessed great progress in
bilateral economic and trade cooperation in recent years. The
trade volume between the two countries amounted to nearly 6
billion U.S. dollars last year, 15 times of that in 1984.
</P>
<P>
The Netherlands ranks fourth among China's European trading
partners, while the Chinese mainland and Hong Kong are the largest
Asian markets for Dutch products.
</P>
</TEXT>
