<HEADLINE> Computer Market to Grow Faster </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The turnover of China's computer
market this year is expected to grow by 18.2 percent over last
year to 175 billion yuan, according to a Ministry of Information
forecast.
</P>
<P>
Experts predict that the impact of the Asian financial crisis
on China's computer market and industry will be lessened in 1999,
and the central government's ongoing expansive fiscal and economic
policies will also boost the growth of this market.
</P>
<P>
Last year, sales in the domestic computer market surged 13.9
percent over the previous year to 148 billion yuan. Of this total,
sales of software products and information services jumped 25
percent to 32.5 billion yuan and sales of hardware products rose
11.1 percent to 115.5 billion yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
