<HEADLINE> WIPO to Hold Inaugural Meeting of Policy Advisory Commission </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The World Intellectual Property
Organization (WIPO) will hold the first meeting of the Policy
Advisory Commission (PAC) on April 15, the United Nations agency
announced here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The PAC, an initiative proposed by Dr Kamil Idris when he took
over as WIPO Director General in November 1997, is composed of
eminent personalities with a proven leadership track-record.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting to be chaired by Idris, PAC members will offer
their insights on the significance of placing intellectual
property in a wider economic, social, and cultural context.
</P>
<P>
"This will help the organization in its quest to demystify
intellectual property which until recently has been seen primarily
as a domain for lawyers and technical information experts," said
WIPO.
</P>
<P>
The PAC will consider how to create broader awareness of the
benefits of a robust intellectual system to spur human creativity
and promote economic development and cultural well-being.
</P>
<P>
The PAC, whose recommendations are not binding, is a purely
advisory body for the Director General of WIPO and does not in any
way replace the decision-making powers of the member states.
</P>
<P>
Song Jian, Vice-Chairman of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference, is expected to be among the 24
participants in the one-day meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
