<HEADLINE> Philippines' New Interior Secretary Sets Priorities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Philippines' Newly-appointed
Secretary of the Department of Interior and Local Government
(DILG) Ronaldo Puno set his top priorities as reform and
modernization programs at the Philippine National Police (PNP),
fire and jail services.
</P>
<P>
Puno, appointed by the Philippine president and concurrent
Secretary of the DILG Joseph Estrada on Monday, took his oath of
office Tuesday in the Presidential Palace.
</P>
<P>
"Upon the guidance of the president, I have to give top
priority to programs that will ensure the effective implementation
of food security, devolution and the fight against illegal drugs,"
Puno said.
</P>
<P>
Also included in his priorities are the expansion of the Street
Watch 117 program nationwide, continuation and creation of new
foreign-assisted program areas, and strengthening and
rationalizing local government corporate power on financing or
projects.
</P>
<P>
Puno also vowed to strengthen the training program for
officials and personnel of the PNP, fire and jail bureaus and
housing program for members of the uniformed sector. 
</P>
