<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tighter Controls on China TV Plays in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- There will be a great increase in
the number of Chinese TV plays to be made this year, as many as 15,
812 are in the works, an increase of 77.8 percent compared with
last year, and the most ever in one year.
</P>
<P>
The State Administration of Radio, Film and Television has
strengthened regulations concerning the production of TV plays,
and plays without certificates will not be permitted, as the
production, publication, and broadcasting of the TV shows will be
under stricter control.
</P>
<P>
One significant change is that among the nationwide TV
production companies applying for permission this year, 62.3
percent are private, exceeding state-owned ones for the first time.
</P>
<P>
There are 36 private TV production companies in Guangdong
Province alone among the applicants, indicating the rapid
privatization and expansion of this sector. 
</P>
</TEXT>
