<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Extravagance, Waste Prohibited in 50th Anniversary Celebrations (Part Two) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
Second, no provinces, government departments, institutions, or
enterprises should engage in activities such as pooling money,
soliciting donations or collecting fees in the name of the 50th
anniversary.
</P>
<P>
Nor is it allowed to issue commercial souvenirs or promote
commercial products or business activities in the name of the 50th
anniversary.
</P>
<P>
Third, celebrations should emphasize effectiveness, be frugal,
exclude extravagance, and guard against formalism.
</P>
<P>
There should be no parades or reviews of troops in any place
other than in the capital city of Beijing. And no grand banquets
are allowed, the circular notes.
</P>
<P>
Fourth, no department of the CPC Central Committee or the
State Council is allowed to hold national conferences or large
exhibitions in Beijing from the beginning of August through
October without prior approval.
</P>
<P>
And the rest of the country should not send any visitors or
tourist groups to Beijing during the three-month period.
</P>
<P>
Fifth, starting at the beginning of September, measures should
be taken to limit the number of people coming to the capital.
</P>
<P>
Sixth, extravagance and waste under the pretext of celebrating
the PRC 50th anniversary are prohibited. All departments concerned
should strengthen supervision and strictly enforce the above-
mentioned principles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
