<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Extravagance, Waste Prohibited in 50th Anniversary Celebrations (Part One) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Extravagance and waste are
strictly prohibited during the celebrations for the 50th
anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China (PRC)
this year, according to a circular issued Today.
</P>
<P>
The circular was jointly issued here by the General Office of
the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and
the General Office of the State Council.
</P>
<P>
"Marking the 50th anniversary of the PRC in a solemn and warm
manner is a major event this year for the Party and the nation,"
the circular says.
</P>
<P>
It is of great importance for the enhancement of patriotic
zeal and national spirit to properly arrange and organize all
celebratory events.
</P>
<P>
However, the celebrations should proceed in accordance with
the principle of solemnity and warmth and proper proportion,
giving priority to effectiveness and frugality, the circular
stresses.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, preparatory activities should not interfere
with the normal work and production, it notes.
</P>
<P>
In order to prohibit extravagance and waste during the
celebrations, the circular stresses the following points:
</P>
<P>
First, there should be no unauthorized building, expansion or
refurbishing of projects under the pretext of greeting the PRC's
50th anniversary.
</P>
<P>
All projects currently under construction should proceed
accordingly, and building quality must be guaranteed.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
