<DOCNO> XIE19990413.0159 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cambodia, China to Enhance Tourism Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Cambodia and China hope to
strengthen their cooperation in tourism to improve the development
of the tourism industry.
</P>
<P>
The two sides expressed the hope at a meeting between the
visiting Director of the Chinese National Tourism Administration
He Guangwei and Cambodian Prime Minister Hun Sen at his Takhmau
residence Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen warmly welcomed Director He and his party to Cambodia.
The two sides exchanged information on tourism in both countries
and believed there is great potential for development.
</P>
<P>
He and his party began their four-day visit on April 10 at the
invitation of the Cambodian Tourism Ministry. The aim of their
visit is to carry out a tourism agreement signed by the two
countries during Prime Minister Hun Sen's visit to China in
February.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen said he believed that their visit will surely boost the
friendly cooperation in tourism between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
While saying great changes had taken place in Cambodia in many
fields, including social orders, Hun Sen pointed out that there is
the need to enhance promotion to increase the confidence of
foreign tourists.
</P>
<P>
He said Cambodia is striving to improve transport,
communications and infrastructure and strengthen security to
attract more foreign tourists. "It is important to develop
Cambodia's tourism," he added.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the prime minister said Cambodia will
consider offering some facilities to Chinese tourists, such as
granting them an entry visa upon landing at the airport.
</P>
<P>
Director He said that with the continuous development of
China's economy and the improvement of the people's living
standard, more and more people will surely hope to travel abroad.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia is rich in scenic spots and cultural heritage. The
centuries-old temples such as Angkor Wat are regarded as some of
the world's most magnificent monuments and were the center of a
Cambodian empire.
</P>
<P>
Tourism is one of Cambodia's most promising industries.
According to Minister of Tourism Veng Serivuth, the number of
tourists this year increased about 25 percent from the same period
of last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
