<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Higher on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Share prices surged on
Singapore Stock Market Tuesday, buoyed by a heavy inflow of
institutional funds which pushed up the market to a new 18-month
high.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index was 18.7 points higher to
finish at 1,679.98 points.
</P>
<P>
The volume increased to 369.86 million units valued at 551.23
million Singapore dollars (about 320.48 million U.S. dollars).
Gainers led losers by 241 to 55 with 135 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
GES was the most heavily traded share with a turnover of 44.97
million shares. It was followed by SingTel which had 12.37 million
shares transacted. EastTech was the next with 12.23 million shares
done.
</P>
<P>
Bukit Sem, SIA, SPH, SP 100 and Venture led the gainers of the
day, increasing by 30 cents each to close at 10.9, 9.7, 22.3, 22.3
and 8.85 Singapore dollars respectively. SIA w00 gained 28 cents
to finish at 3.72 Singapore dollars. Cerebos was 26 cents higher
to end at 3.52 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, UOB F led losers of the day shedding 30 cents
to close at 12.2 Singapore dollars. SIA F fell 20 cents to end at
14.3 Singapore dollars. OCBC F lost 10 cents to finish at 14.2
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said the market also gained support from Wall Street's
overnight rise and the good performances of Asian bourses.
</P>
<P>
They expected the market to break the 1,700-point mark as early
as Wednesday in light of the rapid advance by the local bourse to
smash through one resistance level after another since last week.
</P>
</TEXT>
