<HEADLINE> Don't Waste Chance for Economic Recovery: Estrada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph
Estrada reiterated Tuesday his call on all sectors to unite behind
his administration's efforts to speed up the country's recovery
from the regionwide economic crisis.
</P>
<P>
In a radio interview Tuesday morning, the president said the
Philippines still has the best chance to recover from the crisis
ahead of other countries in Asia and the Pacific and, in fact, has
been showing strong indicators of recovery.
</P>
<P>
"I won't stop thinking and working to uplift the lives of the
poor. The result has so far been good. Our interest rate, for
example, has dropped tremendously, compared to the rate on my
first day in office," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Our economy is doing well. This presents us an opportunity to
unite for economic recovery. Let us not waste this chance,
considering that our neighbors were hit harder by the crisis while
we managed to fare better," Estrada added.
</P>
<P>
The president said his administration has already adopted
business-friendly policies to encourage the business sector to
pursue its role as the government's agent of growth.
</P>
<P>
"It is time for us to help each other. We have been supporting
the private sector by leveling the playing field. We want the
private sector to play an active role in national progress," he
said. 
