<HEADLINE> Annan Willing to Meet Milosevic on Kosovo Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, April 12 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan
said here Monday that he is willing to meet with Yugoslav
President Slobodan Milosevic to find out a way to end the Kosovo
crisis.
</P>
<P>
 Annan, who arrived here Sunday for a two-day official visit
to Spain, made this clear at a press conference held after holding
talks with Spanish Prime Minister Jose Maria Aznar on the
situation in Kosovo, Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The UN head expressed optimism at the perspective of a
political settlement of the conflict in the Balkans, saying he
hadn't given up hope.
</P>
<P>
