<HEADLINE> China to Establish On-Line Hope Schools </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The China Youth Development
Foundation has called on society to help establish on-line Hope
Schools, today's China Youth Daily reports.
</P>
<P>
A China Youth Development Foundation official says that on-line
Hope School teachers and students in outlying areas will get
supplementary teaching materials from the Chinese Education and
Research Net.
</P>
<P>
The China Youth Development Foundation plans to donate an on-
line classroom with 15 computers in each of the one-hundred Hope
Schools this year.
</P>
<P>
The official also said that all Chinese Hope Schools are now
equipped with telephone and electricity supply equipment. With
every village in China linked by telephone next year, on-line
schools will be able to benefit more teachers and students.
</P>
<P>
As one of China's most influential public welfare undertakings,
the Hope Project has raised a 1.6 billion yuan, helped more than
2 million dropout children, and set up over 6,000 Hope Primary
Schools since its founding in October 1989. 
