Singapore Government.
</P>
<P>
Goh, who is on a two-day working visit to Brunei, was making the
remarks to Brunei and painful because
the bottom is made of concrete, not a trampoline."
</P>
<P>
"How soon and how fast each economy recovers will depend not
only on what they do, but also on a global and regional factors,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
While self-praising his own country's short and long term
measures to counter the economic recession and the regional
crisis, he presumed there will be some major risks arising from
other countries including the United States and Japan.
," adding
that "first, the crisis has taken the shine out of ASEAN. Second,
ASEAN as a group is being seen as helpless and worse, disunited in
a crisis."
</P>
<P>
Underlining that the key to recovery is to regain investor
confidence in the reg"
</P>
<P>
"One idea is for ASEAN as a whole to organize joint investment
roadshows to the United States, Europe and Japan to sell the
region, " he said, adding "this could be done in the latter part
of the year after the Indonesian elections."
</P>
