<HEADLINE> Macao Supreme Court to Have Power of Final Adjudication </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Macao's Supreme Court of Justice is
going to exercise the power of final adjudication beginning from
June 1 this year, the Macao Daily News reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted the court's president Manuel Antonio Maduro as
saying that Portugal has empowered the court to handle cases of
final judgment since June. Being a territory ruled by Portugal,
Macao does not enjoy the power of final adjudication.
</P>
<P>
The top judge of Macao made the remarks on Monday while meeting
with a delegation of judges coming from the Chinese mainland.
</P>
<P>
At the invitation of Manuel Antonio Maduro, president of
Macao's Supreme Court of Justice, the delegation arrived in Macao
Monday morning for a five-day tour.
</P>
<P>
As Macao is on the way of returning to the motherland, the
visit would be conducive to the smooth transition and steady
transfer of power in Macao, said Xie Anshan, head of the
delegation.
</P>
<P>
During their talks Monday, Xie Anshan and Manuel Antonio Maduro
exchanged views on the judicial system and judicial structure of
each other, expressing the hope to strengthen the contacts and
cooperation between judicial departments from both sides.
</P>
</TEXT>
