<HEADLINE> Palestinian Statehood Decision on April 27: Envoy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The Palestinian legislature
would meet on April 27 to decide on the issue of Palestinian
statehood, Palestinian envoy to South Africa, Salman El-Herfi,
said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The legislative council would decide whether to unilaterally
declare statehood or postpone it in line with a request from South
African President Nelson Mandela and other world leaders.
</P>
<P>
A decision will be made public on May 4, the date originally
scheduled for the unilateral declaration of the statehood, South
African Press Association quoted El-Herfi as saying.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat met Mandela in Johannesburg on
Monday night, as part of a tour of more than a dozen countries, to
discuss the statehood issue.
</P>
<P>
Arafat hinted in Japan last week that he would not make such a
declaration before Israel's general election on May 17. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
