<HEADLINE> Share prices Rebound in Tokyo on Wall Street Surge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices bounced back in Tokyo
Tuesday following a sharp decline in the previous trading day,
boosted by a surge Monday on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange, which plunged 348.23 points
on Monday, rose 207.76 points, or 1.26 percent, to close at 16,715.
16.
</P>
<P>
Investors had worried Monday that New York stock prices would
fall,after Compaq Computer Corp. said last week it had cut its
earnings forecast for the first quarter of this year, but both the
Dow Jones Industrial Average and the Nasdaq composite index closed
at record highs Monday, boosting Tokyo stock prices, traders said.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, gained 15.54 points or 1.18 percent to 1,331.
74.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section went up to 692.02 million shares
from Monday's 603.65 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Share prices were higher in most business sectors, and traders
noted that issues with relatively low prices in the steel and
construction industries attracted buying, particularly by
individual investors.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, gainers outpaced
losers 821 to 372, with 129 issues ending unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
