<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Close 1.32 Percent Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks rose 154.95
points, or 1.32 percent, to close at 11,899.69 Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Local dealers attributed the increase mainly to the overnight
gains on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
Tuesday's turnover was 5.85 billion HK dollars (750 million
U.S. dollars), 473 million HK dollars (61 million U.S. dollars)
less than that of the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The market opened firmly with the key Hang Seng Index gaining
153.14 points, or 1.30 percent, to close the morning session at
11,897.11.
</P>
<P>
The stocks fell 169.36 points, or 1.42 percent, to close at
11,744.74 Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
