<HEADLINE> Major News Items in leading French Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading French newspapers on Tuesday:
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- After marginalizing Russia in the primary phase of
airstrikes against Yugoslavia, NATO is trying to cuddle Moscow in
order to appease Boris Yeltsin and isolate Slobodan Milosevic. The
foreign ministers' meeting of NATO on Monday also called on U.N.
to be involved in seeking a political solution to the Yugoslav
crisis. The idea of ``international protection'' for Kosovo was
also presented at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
-- German Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder, who was elected
president of the ruling Social Democratic Party, Monday defended
the decision to let Germany to join the NATO military action in
Yugoslavia, the first of its kind since World War II. Germany,
which suffered criminal regime and dictatorship in the past,
cannot close its eyes in front of murder and deportation, he said.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- In his third radio television address since the beginning of
the NATO campaign against Yugoslavia, French President Jacques
Chirac Monday warned his countrymen against what he called ``the
spirit of Munich'' in reference to the Franco-British appeasement
policy toward Nazi Germany. He also called on the United Nations
to play a bigger role in solving the crisis of Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
-- How to put an end to violence dominated the presidential
election campaign in Algeria which ended on Monday. During three
weeks, the seven candidates to succeed Liamine Zeroual toured
around the country but failed to raise the enthusiasm of a people
abused by violence, which has killed from 30,000 to 100,000 people
since 1992.
</P>
</TEXT>
