<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Africa, Botswana Sign Agreement on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 13 (Xinhua) -- South Africa and Botswana
have signed a historic bilateral agreement on the management of
their adjacent national parks, South African Press Association
reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement signed Monday, the Gemsbok National Park in
Botswana and the Kalahari Gemsbok National Park in South Africa
will be managed as a single ecological unit to be known as the
Kgalagadi Transfrontier Park (KTP) .
</P>
<P>
The Kalahari Gemsbok National Park is situated in the
northernmost of Northern Cape Province of South Africa, bordering
with the Gemsbok National Park of Botswana.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of the Kgalagadi Park is the first formally
recognized transfrontier conservation area in southern Africa.
</P>
<P>
The South African National Park said through the establishment
of the transfrontier park, South Africa and Botswana stood to be
benefit through guaranteeing the long-term conservation of the
wildlife resources in the Southern Kalahari which would help
maintain the integrity of the entire Kalahari ecosystem.
</P>
<P>
It would also raise the international profile of the area
through joint promotional campaigns, enhancing its status and
potential as a tourist destination. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
