<HEADLINE> WFP-Aided Project in Ethnic Region Receives Appraisal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Inspecting officials from the World
Food Program gave a positive appraisal to a completed project that
it has aided with 12 million U.S. dollars since 1991 in autonomous
prefectures of the Miao and Tu ethnic minorities in central
China's Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
The project, approved at the organization's 30th Congress in
Rome, includes upgrading water conservation facilities, improving
arid soil, planting trees and grass, building roads, and offering
training in the impoverished region, which is hemmed in by
mountains.
</P>
<P>
All the facilities are now in operation and local environment
has been improved. The officials were informed that food grain
production and per-capita income have increased by 115 percent and
202 percent respectively over the 1991 level. 
</P>
</TEXT>
