<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, April 13 (Xinhua) -- NATO warplanes again bombed
Yugoslav cities of Belgrade, Pancevo, Novi Sad, Kraljevo and Cacak
from Monday night to Tuesday morning, making residents sleepless.
</P>
<P>
At about 01:00 o'clock local time Tuesday, the 21st day of the
alliance's air attacks against Yugoslavia, an unexploded missile
hit a gymnasium in the capital city newly-built for the world
table tennis tournament, according to Belgrade's information
center.
</P>
<P>
At around 3:30, four missiles blasted in an army barracks in
the southern suburbs of the city, the center said.
</P>
<P>
