<HEADLINE> Manila Adopts Three-pronged Job Generation Strategy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government is
adopting a three-pronged job preservation and generation strategy
to offset the rise in the unemployment rate, which, it said, is
likely to drop with the recovery of agriculture and the robust
growth of the services sector this year.
</P>
<P>
Presidential Spokesman Jerry Barican said Tuesday that the
three-pronged job preservation and generation strategy involves
the following:
</P>
<P>
-- Improvements in the labor market information system,
particularly in job matching. This includes the Philippine
Employment Service Offices and the Philippines-Jobnet.
</P>
<P>
-- Labor-management cooperation, promotion of tripartism,
employment flexibility and worker empowerment.
</P>
<P>
-- Reforms in the labor and employment programs such as the
Workers' Retraining Program, National Apprenticeship Program and
Occupational Health and Safety Programs.
</P>
<P>
Last Monday, Barican said the reported increase in unemployment
stemmed from the huge expansion of the country's labor force.
</P>
<P>
The country's unemployment rate increased to 9.0 percent in
January 1999, or 0.6 percent higher compared to the same period
last year. 
</P>
