<HEADLINE> 102 Goals Scored in Group Matches at Youth Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 13 (Xinhua) -- A total of 102 goals were scored in
the group matches of the on-going 10th World Youth Soccer
Championship which opened here on April 3.
</P>
<P>
Group F featuring Spain, Brazil, Zambia and Honduras produced
the highest number of goals, 22, followed by Group A with 18.
</P>
<P>
Brazil has the sharpest attack scoring eight goals in three
matches of the first round, followed by Mali, Japan, Ireland and
Croatia with six each.
</P>
<P>
England paraded the most blunt attack, scoring no goal in three
games. They were followed by Kazakhstan and Argentina with a goal
each in as many matches.
</P>
<P>
In addition, England, along with Honduras and Kazakhstan,
recorded no point each having lost all their three games. Spain,
Ghana, Argentina and Ireland showed how miserly they were as they
conceded only one goal each in three games, followed by Croatia,
Mexico and Uruguay with two each.
</P>
<P>
At the other end, Honduras showed how porous their defence was
conceding 10 goals in three games followed by Kazakhstan with nine
goals while Australia and Zambia gave away eight goals each.
</P>
<P>
Brazil and Croatia scored the highest number of goals in a game.
Brazil mauled Zambia 5-1 while Croatia demolished Kazakhstan by
the same margin.
</P>
<P>
The South American region showed how powerful they are in
soccer when all four representatives -- Brazil, Argentina, Uruguay
and Paraguay -- made it to the second round.
</P>
<P>
Africa put four teams -- Nigeria, Ghana, Mali and Cameroon --
into the second round. The fifth, Zambia, crashed out. Four
European nations -- Spain, Croatia, Ireland and Portugal -- out of
six got second round berths. England and Germany have returned
home.
</P>
<P>
Asia showed it is the weakest region in youth soccer when three
of its representatives out of four were bundled out in the first
round.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia, Kazakhstan and South Korea are headed for home,
leaving out Japan to carry the region's flag. Oceania's sole
representative Australia failed to go through.
</P>
<P>
With 102 goals in group matches, the 10th World Youth
Championship tagged Nigeria '99 has shown that it is a high
scoring championship. In Qatar '95, a total of 105 goals were
scored throughout the championship, but only 16 teams took part in
that tournament against Nigeria '99's 24.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia '97 recorded 165 goals in all. 
</P>
</TEXT>
