reduce their production costs, the Nation newspaper reported
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the ministry said the government will soon
announce the cut in import duties as a follow-up to an economic
stimulus package announced on March 30.
</P>
<P>
He said the duties will be cut from the current range of 0
percent to 30 percent to a new range of 0 percent to 20 percent.
</P>
<P>
About nine categories of goods will face the axe, and their
average tax rate will fall by half from the current 17 percent. (
Thailand-Import Duties)
