<HEADLINE> Two Killed in Manila as Tanker Hits Skyway Post </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- A driver and his helper were
killed when a 10-wheeler tanker hit one of the giant posts of the
Skyway along the South Expressway of Manila Monday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Police identified the fatalities as Gilbert Tulin, 28, driver
of tanker and Christopher Cabuco, helper.
</P>
<P>
Police said the accident occurred at about 12:51 p.m. Monday
while Tulin was driving the tanker along the expressway.
</P>
<P>
Tulin apparently lost control of his speeding tanker and
smashed against of the giant posts of the Skyway.
</P>
<P>
Tulin and Cabuco were rushed to the South Superhighway Medical
Center but Cabuco was pronounced dead on arrival by an attending
physician.
</P>
<P>
Tulin lost his leg first and was diagnosed in critical
condition. He later died Monday night. 
