<HEADLINE> China Criticizes India for Missile Test (More Added) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- China today criticized India for
testing a medium-range ballistic missile, saying that it is a
violation of UN resolutions that may trigger off a new arms race
in south Asia.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese side expresses regret and concern over this," said
Foreign Ministry spokesman Sun Yuxi at today's routine press
conference.
</P>
<P>
He said: "The UN Security Council Resolution 1172 called on
India to cease the development of ballistic missiles capable of
delivering nuclear weapons."
</P>
<P>
The missile test by India on April 11 violated the letters and
the guidelines of above-mentioned resolution and could possibly
trigger off a new round of arms race in South Asia, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese side took note of the trend that India and
Pakistan had strengthened dialogue in the past months and
increased trust and achieved certain results, Sun said.
</P>
<P>
He said: "The Chinese side hopes that the two countries will
peacefully resolve the differences and issues between them through
patient, frank and meaningful dialogue. This conforms to the
fundamental interests of the people of South Asia." 
</P>
