<HEADLINE> Beijing to Host Conference on Innovative Medicine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- An international conference to
discuss innovative therapies based on the integration of modern
and traditional medicines will be held in Beijing late this month.
</P>
<P>
The first World Conference on Innovative Integrated Medicine
will not only focus on theories and technologies but also display
new products, according to the conference organizer, the Chinese
Health Care Association on Ageing.
</P>
<P>
"It is important for China, which has a thousand-year-long
history of using traditional medicines, to hold such an event as
medical treatment is entering a new era with the rapid growth of
life sciences," said Liu Shu from the conference's organizing
committee.
</P>
<P>
More than 400 Chinese scientists and their counterparts from
the United States, Canada, Australia, Japan, India and other
countries will hold seminars on genetic engineering, new therapies,
geriatrics, rehabilitation research, and the modernization of
traditional Chinese medicine.  
</P>
