BANGKOK April 13 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's Finance Ministry is
working on cutting import duties for various products to help
domestic manufacturers reduce their production costs, the Nation
newspaper reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the ministry said the government will soon
announce the cut in import duties as a follow-up to an economic
stimulus package announced on March 30.
</P>
<P>
