<HEADLINE> Law Books Selling like Hot Cakes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The death sentence handed down
recently on an official held responsible for a bridge collapse
which killed forty people has sparked off a huge interest in law
books amongst construction firms and relevant officials.
</P>
<P>
According to the Beijing Book Mansion,the largest book store
in Asia, copies of the four major construction laws were among the
stores top 10 best sellers in March, and hundreds of books and law
reports are being sold every day.
</P>
<P>
Since March 1 through April 12, the bookstore sold 4,234
copies of the Contract Law, 1,856 copies of the Constitution and 1,
235 copies of the Law on Product Quality.
</P>
<P>
The infamous incident of the collapsed Qijiang bridge in
southwest China's Qijiang County and the subsequent sentences has
sounded alarm bells amongst the country's construction contractors.
</P>
<P>
The 180 meter long by seven meter wide Rainbow Bridge collapsed
on January 4th, killing 40 people. Another 14 people were injured
and damage was estimated at 6.31 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Investigations show that the steel bridge, erected by a private
contractor in February 1996, was of inferior quality, and that the
accident resulted from official dereliction of duty and loopholes
in engineering and construction.
</P>
<P>
Lin Shiyuan, former deputy secretary of the Qijiang County
Committee of the Communist Party of China, was sentenced to death
for taking bribes and for dereliction of duty in the nationally
televised trial in early April which attracted hundreds of
millions of viewers. Others involved were given heavy jail
sentences and fines.
</P>
<P>
A buyer of 10 copies of the Criminal Law and another 10 copies
of the Law on Product Quality said that he is an inspection
officer for construction quality, and was planning to open a
course for construction contractors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
