Premier Zhu Rongji on a substantial down payment towards Beijing's
entry to the WTO," the paper said in a lengthy editorial.
</P>
<P>
"Although a final deal is not yet done, and important gaps
remain, the quality of the package makes it likely, if not yet
inevitable," it said.
</P>
<P>
"China and the United States should capitalize on the progress
made last week and work to close the deal well in advance of the
November launch of global trade talks," the paper said. 
