<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Henan Boosts Social Security System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Henan Province
has been redoubling efforts to make the social security network
cover more people.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, old-age insurance policies will
increase to 6.28 million by the end of the year, a net rise of 1.
45 million people over the present 4.83 million.
</P>
<P>
As a result the province will see a rise of 1.05 billion yuan
in its total old-age insurance premiums, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, the province is expected to have 7.54 million
workers taking out unemployment insurance policies by the end of
this year, a rise of 3.55 million over 1998. And the fund levied
from employers against unemployment will amount to 940 million
yuan by the end of 1999.
</P>
<P>
Information from the provincial bureau of labor and social
security said that 53 percent of the province's workers have taken
out unemployment insurance policies, and another 73.2 percent of
its workers have taken out old-age insurance policies, both higher
than the national averages.
</P>
<P>
So far, the number of people taking out insurance policies to
cater for old age, jobless, work accidents and medical costs
amount to 13 million in the province, most of whom are people
working in enterprises. 
</P>
</TEXT>
