<HEADLINE> NATO's Advance Forces Arrive in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, April 12 (Xinhua) -- A detachment of about 270 French
soldiers arrived at the Adriatic port of Durres Monday morning by
the cargo ship "Orage", Albanian television Klan reported.
</P>
<P>
The detachment is the advance force of 8,000 NATO soldiers, who
will support the U.N. High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) in
providing relief efforts for some 300,000 ethnic Albanians pouring
into Albania from the neighboring province of Kosovo in Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Three helicopters, 50 fire engines and 110 other vehicles were
also transported to Durres.
</P>
<P>
Of the 270 French soldiers, some were immediately flown by
helicopters to Rinas airport near Tirana, while others were
deployed at Durres.
</P>
<P>
Sources of the Albanian Defense Ministry said the rest of
NATO's follow-up troops would soon arrive in Albania.
</P>
<P>
NATO's council Sunday approved the deployment in Albania of 8,
000 soldiers from four countries, including Italy and France.
</P>
