<HEADLINE> Renault Eyeing China's Special Vehicle Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The French car manufacturer Renault
has recently changed its China operations strategy and will
concentrate on producing automobiles for special uses.
</P>
<P>
The largest automobile producer in France believes there is a
big potential for specialized vehicles in China and has developed
19 varieties, such as ambulances, cash-security vans, police cars,
post office vehicles and container trucks.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman from the company said here recently that Renault
will accelerate the development and production of special vehicles
in China in an effort to adapt to changing market trends.
</P>
<P>
The company increased its investment in China last year by
consolidating its luxury passenger bus market, which helped expand
the production capacity of its 98 million-U.S. dollar joint
venture with China Sanjiang Space Technology Group to 20,000 "
Traffic" mini buses annually.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture Sanjiang Renault Automotive Co. Ltd. in Wuhan,
provincial capital of Hubei in central China, manufactured and
sold 1,600 "Traffic" buses last year and improved its after-sales
service network in 60 cities throughout China. 
