<HEADLINE> China Destroys Low-quality Medicines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua)-- The State Drug Administration SDA)
destroyed 183 batches of fake and sub-standard medicines during
the first quarter this year, today's "China Daily" reports.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing-based English newspaper quotes administration
officials as saying that nine pharmaceutical manufacturers were
ordered to stop producing eight varieties of medicines.
</P>
<P>
The medicines in question were deemed, during random quality
tests between January and March, to be below national standards.
</P>
<P>
Administration officials tested 1,650 batches of 690 varieties
of medicines, of which 11.1 percent were deemed to be sub-standard.
</P>
<P>
The administration revoked business licenses from three trade
units caught marketing fake medicines. The units were in south
China's Guangdong Province, and central Hubei and Henan provinces.
</P>
</TEXT>
