<HEADLINE> Forest Fire Causes Evacuation of 800 Cubans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Cuban authorities announced Monday
that 800 people will be evacuated from an area in western Cuban
because of a forest fire that is burning out of control.
</P>
<P>
The fire started on April 8 in the far west of the island,
known as "Las Delicias," where there is an abundance of pine and
eucalyptus trees. Around 6,000 hectares of the forest are
reportedly burning, but no casualties have been reported.
</P>
<P>
Three planes have conducted 14 flights over the area to douse
the flames with water. The cause of the fire is still under
investigation.
</P>
<P>
According to meteorological sources, the Caribbean region
shared by western Cuba and the southern United States is now under
the influence of dry air currents, which hinders the fighting
against this kind of fire. 
</P>
