<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Arrives in New York </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji
arrived here on Monday night to continue his eight-day official
visit to the United States at the invitation of U.S. President
Bill Clinton.
</P>
<P>
Upon his arrival, Premier Zhu was greeted by the local Chinese
community and officials of the eastern states of New York and New
Jersey.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in New York, the fifth leg of his U.S. tour,
Zhu is scheduled to visit the NASDAQ Stock Market, the world's
first electronic-based and fastest growing stock market.
</P>
<P>
Zhu, who started his visit to the United States on April 6, is
the first Chinese premier to visit the country in 15 years.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the Chinese premier toured Los Angeles, Washington D.C.
, Denver and Chicago.
</P>
<P>
Before leaving Washington for Denver last Saturday, the Chinese
premier issued a joint statement with President Clinton, in which
the United States commits to working harder for China's entry into
the World Trade Organization (WTO) in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Also on Saturday, the two countries signed an agreement on U.S.-
China agricultural cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Zhu will leave for Boston, the last stop of his U.S. visit, on
Wednesday morning. 
