<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Juventus Suffers Zidane Scare </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Italian soccer club Juventus star
Zinedine Zidane has given Manchester United a boost ahead of next
week's Champions' League semi-final second leg after the French
midfielder suffered a recurrence of his knee injury.
</P>
<P>
According to local reports on Monday, Zidane was out for three
weeks with a twisted knee before last Wednesday's first leg but
was outstanding on his return in the 1-1 draw at Old Trafford.
</P>
<P>
However, the injury problem flared up again during Sunday's
game against Bologna, forcing the World Player of the Year to be
substituted at half-time.
</P>
<P>
"I didn't come out for the second half because the joint was
giving me trouble," Zidane said. "I told the coach that I didn't
want to go on and he agreed.
</P>
<P>
"But it's strange all the same. I didn't feel anything for the
90 minutes in Manchester but here all it needed was 45 minutes to
cause me problems."
</P>
<P>
Juventus, who face Italian league leaders Lazio on Saturday,
will have to decide later this week whether to risk the World Cup-
winning midfielder. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990413.0337 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE>   Utah's Karl Malone Named NBA Player of The Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Utah's Karl Malone, who led
the Jazz to a 4-0 record last week, today was named NBA Player of
the Week for games played Monday, April 5, through Sunday, April
11.
</P>
<P>
Malone averaged 28.8 points, 10.5 rebounds, 3.7 assists and 2.0
steals per game, while shooting .573 (39-for-68) from the field
and .802(37-for-42) from the free throw line. He ranked second in
scoring, ninth in field-goal percentage, and tied for 11th in
rebounding among league leaders for the week.
</P>
<P>
"I believe that might have been the finest week of Malone's
career," said Jazz head coach Jerry Sloan. "We probably wouldn't
have won once this week without him. He's won a lot of games for
us over the years. And he knows what he has to do. Nobody tells
him. He just keeps on doing it."
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday at the Los Angeles Lakers, Malone set a franchise
record by shooting 12-for-12 from the field, scoring 30 points,
grabbing 10 rebounds and handing out five assists in a Jazz win.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, he had 38 points, 12 rebounds and five assists in
a defeat of Golden State. Friday night, he recorded 31 points, 10
rebounds, three assists and two steals against Phoenix.
</P>
<P>
Malone made three consecutive free throws with six-tenths of a
second remaining in the game to propel the Jazz to a 93-92 victory
over the Suns at the Delta Center. The Mailman closed the week
with 16 points, 10 rebounds and two assists in an 85-76 victory
over Houston Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Other candidates for NBA Player of the Week were Cleveland's
Shawn Kemp, Dallas' Gary Trent, Denver's Nick Van Exel, Detroit's
Grant Hill, Miami's Alonzo Mourning, Orlando's Anfernee Hardaway,
Phoenix's Jason Kidd and Clifford Robinson, and Sacramento's Chris
Webber. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
