<HEADLINE> Karl Malone Banned One Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Karl Malone of the Utah Jazz
was fined $4,000 and suspended one game for throwing a punch and
Anthony Johnson of the Atlanta Hawks will miss one game and pay $5,
000 for throwing a elbow.
</P>
<P>
The NBA announced the suspension and fines today. Malone was
penalized for throwing a punch at Othella Harrington of Houston on
Sunday, while Johnson's penalty resulted from elbowing Bob Sura of
Cleveland, also on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Malone will miss Monday night's game against Vancouver, and
Johnson will sit out Tuesday game against Milwaukee.
</P>
<P>
Atlanta's Dikembe Mutombo was fined $7,500 for elbowing Chris
Childs of New York last Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
