<HEADLINE> Mexican Stocks Close High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Mexican stocks closed high
Monday with the key IPC index of 5,303.28 points, rising 98.4
points or by 1.89 percent than the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The volume amounted to some 133.001 million U.S. dollars traded
on 83.685 million shares against the 63.635 million shares worth
110.479 million dollars last Friday.
</P>
<P>
Stock analysts here said the soaring reflected the influence of
New York exchanges, which showed bullish again with the average
Dow Jones industrial average of 10,339.51 on Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
